      "description": "This E46 M3 is a driver-focused example featuring the high-revving S54B32 inline-six engine equipped with individual throttle bodies and a dual-VANOS variable valve timing system. Power is sent to the rear wheels via a Getrag 6-speed manual transmission and a variable M differential lock. To ensure long-term structural integrity, the rear subframe has been reinforced with plates, and the rod bearings have been addressed. The suspension retains its factory MacPherson strut front and multi-link rear setup, providing the telepathic handling these chassis are known for. While the Alpine White paint shows minor road use, the mechanical vitals are strong, featuring a recent valve adjustment and a cooling system refresh with an aluminum radiator.",
